07/10/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer called for full adherence to the Ohrid Peace Accords, in an interview Wednesday (6 October) with Skopje's A1 TV.
Asked to comment on next month's referendum on the new decentralisation laws, de Hoop Scheffer said the public has a constitutional right to hold referenda and express its will.
But he urged voters to remember that the Ohrid Agreement calls for decentralisation.
In other news, Skopje is hosting a two-day conference on judicial reforms.
Representatives from other Balkan countries and the EU are attending.
On Wednesday meanwhile, Macedonia and Turkey agreed to excise passages from textbooks that could potentially fuel ethnic tensions.
The decision came during talks between the respective education ministers in Skopje.
(Makfax, Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 07/10/04;
A1 TV - 06/10/04)
